Draft the “FINANCIAL INFORMATION” section of an IPO prospectus based strictly on the evidence provided below.

REQUIRED STRUCTURE

12. FINANCIAL INFORMATION

12.1 Basis of Preparation
- Describe the accounting standards applied.
- State audit status and financial period coverage.
- Include standard cross-references where applicable.

12.2 Historical Financial Information
- Introduce the historical financial statements.
- State what periods are covered.
- Do NOT interpret results.

12.2.1 Statements of Profit or Loss and Other Comprehensive Income
- Introduce the table and what it presents.
- Do NOT analyse or explain performance.
- Do NOT repeat all figures in text.

12.2.2 Statements of Financial Position
- Introduce the table and what it presents.
- Describe asset, equity and liability classifications at a high level only.

12.2.3 Statements of Cash Flows (if provided)
- Introduce the table and coverage period.
- Do NOT analyse cash movements.

12.3 Key Financial Definitions (if applicable)
- Provide definitions exactly as disclosed (e.g. EBITDA, EPS).
- Include calculation notes only if explicitly provided.

For each subsection:
- Use short paragraphs.
- Include references in the format:
  [doc_name | page/section]

